<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="35" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="35">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="35">
<emphasis bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="35">LM</emphasis>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Surirella wufluminensis sp. nov., LM, x 400 A, C two counter-clockwise twisted valves B, D two clockwise twisted valves. Micrograph of the holotype specimen (Fig. A) and isotype specimen (Fig. D). Scale bar: 50 μm." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.201.79626.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/703850" pageId="0" pageNumber="35">1</figureCitation>
). Valves twisted, sometimes exhibiting linear-lanceolate valve outline (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Surirella wufluminensis sp. nov., LM, x 400 A, C two counter-clockwise twisted valves B, D two clockwise twisted valves. Micrograph of the holotype specimen (Fig. A) and isotype specimen (Fig. D). Scale bar: 50 μm." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.201.79626.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/703850" pageId="0" pageNumber="35">1D</figureCitation>
), with twisted and deflected apices (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Surirella wufluminensis sp. nov., LM, x 400 A, C two counter-clockwise twisted valves B, D two clockwise twisted valves. Micrograph of the holotype specimen (Fig. A) and isotype specimen (Fig. D). Scale bar: 50 μm." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.201.79626.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/703850" pageId="0" pageNumber="35">1A-C</figureCitation>
). Valve dimensions (n = 27): 198-295 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
long, 41-50 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
wide. Valve face smooth without undulations, valve midline sigmoid, fibulae very distinctive, 20-28 in 100 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
. The degree of rotation (twist) of the valves differs (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Surirella wufluminensis sp. nov., LM, x 400 A, C two counter-clockwise twisted valves B, D two clockwise twisted valves. Micrograph of the holotype specimen (Fig. A) and isotype specimen (Fig. D). Scale bar: 50 μm." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.201.79626.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/703850" pageId="0" pageNumber="35">1A-D</figureCitation>
) as each position relative to the observer is different. Two type valves are observed under LM: one is counterclockwise twisted (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Surirella wufluminensis sp. nov., LM, x 400 A, C two counter-clockwise twisted valves B, D two clockwise twisted valves. Micrograph of the holotype specimen (Fig. A) and isotype specimen (Fig. D). Scale bar: 50 μm." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.201.79626.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/703850" pageId="0" pageNumber="35">1A, C</figureCitation>
), the other is clockwise twisted (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Surirella wufluminensis sp. nov., LM, x 400 A, C two counter-clockwise twisted valves B, D two clockwise twisted valves. Micrograph of the holotype specimen (Fig. A) and isotype specimen (Fig. D). Scale bar: 50 μm." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.201.79626.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/703850" pageId="0" pageNumber="35">1B, D</figureCitation>
), also seen in SEM (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Surirella wufluminensis sp. nov., SEM A-C three valves in external view; note the visual discrepancies of twist degrees between them as the position of each valve relative to the observer differs D-F three valves in internal view; note the visual discrepancies of twist degrees between them. Scale bars: 20 μm." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.201.79626.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/703851" pageId="0" pageNumber="35">2A-F</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption doi="10.3897/phytokeys.201.79626.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/703851" pageId="0" pageNumber="35" start="Figure 2" startId="F2">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="35">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="35">Figure 2.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bing Liu &amp; Kociolek" authorityYear="2022" class="Bacillariophyceae" family="Surirellaceae" genus="Surirella" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Surirella wufluminensis" order="Surirellales" pageId="0" pageNumber="35" phylum="Bacillariophyta" rank="species" species="wufluminensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="35">Surirella wufluminensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov., SEM 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="35">A-C</emphasis>
three valves in external view; note the visual discrepancies of twist degrees between them as the position of each valve relative to the observer differs 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="35">D-F</emphasis>
three valves in internal view; note the visual discrepancies of twist degrees between them. Scale bars: 20 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="35">
<emphasis bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="35">SEM</emphasis>
(Figs 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Surirella wufluminensis sp. nov., SEM A-C three valves in external view; note the visual discrepancies of twist degrees between them as the position of each valve relative to the observer differs D-F three valves in internal view; note the visual discrepancies of twist degrees between them. Scale bars: 20 μm." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.201.79626.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/703851" pageId="0" pageNumber="35">2</figureCitation>
- 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Surirella wufluminensis sp. nov., internal view, SEM A-C middle details from Fig. 2 D, note that fibulae extend 1 / 3 to 1 / 2 of half valve width (A), one portula between two adjacent fibulae (A, B), uniseriate striae, and valve mantle with thickened base margin (C, white arrow) D, E apical details from Fig. 2 D, note two interrupted external terminal raphe endings (D, two arrows), two helictoglossa-like processes (E, two arrows) F another apex showing continuous raphe at one apex (white arrow). Scale bars: 5 μm (A); 2 μm (B-F)." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.201.79626.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/703865" pageId="0" pageNumber="35">4</figureCitation>
). Valve twisted, but visual discrepancies of degree of twist differs (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Surirella wufluminensis sp. nov., SEM A-C three valves in external view; note the visual discrepancies of twist degrees between them as the position of each valve relative to the observer differs D-F three valves in internal view; note the visual discrepancies of twist degrees between them. Scale bars: 20 μm." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.201.79626.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/703851" pageId="0" pageNumber="35">2A-F</figureCitation>
). Valve surface flat without undulations but mound-like siliceous outgrowths scattered throughout (Figs 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Surirella wufluminensis sp. nov., SEM A-C three valves in external view; note the visual discrepancies of twist degrees between them as the position of each valve relative to the observer differs D-F three valves in internal view; note the visual discrepancies of twist degrees between them. Scale bars: 20 μm." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.201.79626.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/703851" pageId="0" pageNumber="35">2A-C</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Surirella wufluminensis sp. nov., external view, SEM A a whole valve B middle detail from A showing the shallow depressions on the valve face correspond to the ones on the mantle (four arrows) C-E details from Fig. B showing mound-like siliceous outgrowths on the valve surface (C, D, three wavy arrows respectively), raised longitudinal ridges on both sides of the raphe (C, two arrows), slit-like external openings of areolae on both valve face and mantle (D-F) F, G apical details from A, note interrupted terminal raphe endings (see also Fig. 4 D). Scale bars: 20 μm (A); 3 μm (B, C, F, G); 1 μm (D, E)." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.201.79626.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/703864" pageId="0" pageNumber="35">3A-D</figureCitation>
). Very shallow depressions close to mantle, corresponding to beneath, internal fibulae (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Surirella wufluminensis sp. nov., external view, SEM A a whole valve B middle detail from A showing the shallow depressions on the valve face correspond to the ones on the mantle (four arrows) C-E details from Fig. B showing mound-like siliceous outgrowths on the valve surface (C, D, three wavy arrows respectively), raised longitudinal ridges on both sides of the raphe (C, two arrows), slit-like external openings of areolae on both valve face and mantle (D-F) F, G apical details from A, note interrupted terminal raphe endings (see also Fig. 4 D). Scale bars: 20 μm (A); 3 μm (B, C, F, G); 1 μm (D, E)." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.201.79626.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/703864" pageId="0" pageNumber="35">3B</figureCitation>
, four arrows). Raised longitudinal ridges produced on both sides of raphe (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Surirella wufluminensis sp. nov., external view, SEM A a whole valve B middle detail from A showing the shallow depressions on the valve face correspond to the ones on the mantle (four arrows) C-E details from Fig. B showing mound-like siliceous outgrowths on the valve surface (C, D, three wavy arrows respectively), raised longitudinal ridges on both sides of the raphe (C, two arrows), slit-like external openings of areolae on both valve face and mantle (D-F) F, G apical details from A, note interrupted terminal raphe endings (see also Fig. 4 D). Scale bars: 20 μm (A); 3 μm (B, C, F, G); 1 μm (D, E)." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.201.79626.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/703864" pageId="0" pageNumber="35">3C</figureCitation>
). Externally, costae (thickened silica ribs) absent, external openings of areolae slit-like on both valve face and mantle (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Surirella wufluminensis sp. nov., external view, SEM A a whole valve B middle detail from A showing the shallow depressions on the valve face correspond to the ones on the mantle (four arrows) C-E details from Fig. B showing mound-like siliceous outgrowths on the valve surface (C, D, three wavy arrows respectively), raised longitudinal ridges on both sides of the raphe (C, two arrows), slit-like external openings of areolae on both valve face and mantle (D-F) F, G apical details from A, note interrupted terminal raphe endings (see also Fig. 4 D). Scale bars: 20 μm (A); 3 μm (B, C, F, G); 1 μm (D, E)." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.201.79626.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/703864" pageId="0" pageNumber="35">3D, E</figureCitation>
). External distal raphe endings interrupted at both apices (Figs 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Surirella wufluminensis sp. nov., external view, SEM A a whole valve B middle detail from A showing the shallow depressions on the valve face correspond to the ones on the mantle (four arrows) C-E details from Fig. B showing mound-like siliceous outgrowths on the valve surface (C, D, three wavy arrows respectively), raised longitudinal ridges on both sides of the raphe (C, two arrows), slit-like external openings of areolae on both valve face and mantle (D-F) F, G apical details from A, note interrupted terminal raphe endings (see also Fig. 4 D). Scale bars: 20 μm (A); 3 μm (B, C, F, G); 1 μm (D, E)." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.201.79626.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/703864" pageId="0" pageNumber="35">3F, G</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Surirella wufluminensis sp. nov., internal view, SEM A-C middle details from Fig. 2 D, note that fibulae extend 1 / 3 to 1 / 2 of half valve width (A), one portula between two adjacent fibulae (A, B), uniseriate striae, and valve mantle with thickened base margin (C, white arrow) D, E apical details from Fig. 2 D, note two interrupted external terminal raphe endings (D, two arrows), two helictoglossa-like processes (E, two arrows) F another apex showing continuous raphe at one apex (white arrow). Scale bars: 5 μm (A); 2 μm (B-F)." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.201.79626.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/703865" pageId="0" pageNumber="35">4D</figureCitation>
). Internally, distal raphe endings interrupted only at one apex where two helictoglossa-like processes present (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Surirella wufluminensis sp. nov., internal view, SEM A-C middle details from Fig. 2 D, note that fibulae extend 1 / 3 to 1 / 2 of half valve width (A), one portula between two adjacent fibulae (A, B), uniseriate striae, and valve mantle with thickened base margin (C, white arrow) D, E apical details from Fig. 2 D, note two interrupted external terminal raphe endings (D, two arrows), two helictoglossa-like processes (E, two arrows) F another apex showing continuous raphe at one apex (white arrow). Scale bars: 5 μm (A); 2 μm (B-F)." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.201.79626.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/703865" pageId="0" pageNumber="35">4E</figureCitation>
